00:50:58.720 --> 00:51:01.860
rectangular or square...

00:51:01.860 --> 00:51:04.980
Yes, please.

00:51:14.130 --> 00:51:16.430
&gt;&gt;AUDIENCE MEMBER: (inaudible)

00:51:37.720 --> 00:51:40.110
&gt;&gt;HEBA: Yes, sure.

00:51:40.110 --> 00:51:44.830
As for prayers- during the time
of the Rightly Guided Khalifs,

00:51:44.830 --> 00:51:47.210
women used to pray behind men,

00:51:47.210 --> 00:51:50.150
but they were not separated
from the men.

00:51:50.150 --> 00:51:53.130
So, just behind them.

00:51:53.130 --> 00:51:58.440
But, after that, during the
Ummayid era, we have no record

00:51:58.440 --> 00:52:01.180
that they were also
separated from men.

00:52:01.180 --> 00:52:04.540
So, probably they would have
been praying behind the men

00:52:04.540 --> 00:52:09.840 position:56%
and it happened like that all the
time probably until the Ottoman time

00:52:09.840 --> 00:52:13.050
when we started to see
a sort of a separation

00:52:13.050 --> 00:52:17.080
by providing a specific
place for women to pray in-

00:52:17.080 --> 00:52:20.450
separated from the place for men.

00:52:20.450 --> 00:52:21.840
This is for prayer.

00:52:21.840 --> 00:52:28.060
As for education, we have
records of historians telling us

00:52:28.060 --> 00:52:32.460
that families were
sending their children,

00:52:32.460 --> 00:52:35.380
I mean female children, the girls.

00:52:35.380 --> 00:52:39.820
They would send them to private
katatib to receive education.

00:52:39.820 --> 00:52:44.140
Okay? So, children, I mean
the girls were also taught,

00:52:44.140 --> 00:52:47.890
but probably they were taught
only the elementary education,

00:52:47.890 --> 00:52:51.620
so they received only the
elementary education and the

00:52:51.620 --> 00:52:56.540
of course those are the wealthy
family only, but the common people

00:52:56.540 --> 00:52:59.870
who are in the middle class,
it would be hard for them

00:52:59.870 --> 00:53:05.630
to send their girls for- to
receive education in the kattab.

00:53:05.630 --> 00:53:09.470
But, during the Mamluk period
I told you that my thesis was

00:53:09.470 --> 00:53:13.790
about the katatib in
the Mamluk period.

00:53:13.790 --> 00:53:19.350
I realize that during the Mamluk
period, there were some katatibs

00:53:19.350 --> 00:53:25.440
for girls only and some other
katatibs for boys and some

00:53:25.440 --> 00:53:32.190
of the elite of the society would
continue to send their girls

00:53:32.190 --> 00:53:40.460 position:56%
to a specific sheik or teacher in
order to give them higher education.

00:53:40.460 --> 00:53:44.090
So we have records about women
who were reciting the Quran

00:53:44.090 --> 00:53:48.750
or telling hadis after the
prophet Mohammed or a famous woman

00:53:48.750 --> 00:53:53.220
who were historians so that
appeared but only in medieval times

00:53:53.220 --> 00:53:57.180
in Eesef Egypt which
I can tell about.

00:53:57.180 --> 00:53:58.480
Thank you.

00:53:58.480 --> 00:54:00.780
Yes?

00:54:06.730 --> 00:54:09.030
&gt;&gt;AUDIENCE MEMBER: (inaudible)

00:54:18.500 --> 00:54:19.800
&gt;&gt;HEBA: Yes, sure.

00:54:19.800 --> 00:54:22.900
They are preserved actually the
ministry of tourism together

00:54:22.900 --> 00:54:29.680
with the Ministry of Archaeology
are paying or doing so much effort

00:54:29.680 --> 00:54:32.850
to preserve those buildings,
especially in Cairo.

00:54:32.850 --> 00:54:36.580
We have more than 500
Islamic buildings in Cairo.

00:54:36.580 --> 00:54:40.340
You know that Cairo was known
as the City of Southern Minarets

00:54:40.340 --> 00:54:43.120
because it chose to have more
than a thousand buildings

00:54:43.120 --> 00:54:48.260
of Islamic architecture,
but the number was reduced.

00:54:48.260 --> 00:54:52.620
But, they are doing so much
effort to preserve those buildings

00:54:52.620 --> 00:54:56.630
and paying so much to
maintain them and some

00:54:56.630 --> 00:55:01.090
of them are offering guiding
tours or guided tours also.

00:55:01.090 --> 00:55:06.730
But, the problem about Islamic
architecture is that it is mingling

00:55:06.730 --> 00:55:09.240
with the community- it is,

00:55:09.240 --> 00:55:11.860
if you want to see the
Islamic architecture,

00:55:11.860 --> 00:55:15.920
you would go to the narrowest
streets of Cairo and you would go

00:55:15.920 --> 00:55:20.360
to inhabited districts
or neighborhoods.

00:55:20.360 --> 00:55:25.040
So, it is not in a separate tourism
area, but it is within the city.

00:55:25.040 --> 00:55:27.340
&gt;&gt;AUDIENCE MEMBER: (inaudible)

00:55:42.550 --> 00:55:44.570
&gt;&gt;HEBA: No, actually
they moved away.

00:55:44.570 --> 00:55:49.500
The effort of Hassan Fatri,
the architect that I mentioned.

00:55:49.500 --> 00:55:54.930
To my knowledge, the only effort
to revive the Islamic architecture.

00:55:54.930 --> 00:55:58.290
It happened in a specific period
during the Ottoman period.

00:55:58.290 --> 00:56:03.580
There was a revival to the Mamluk
architecture in particular.

00:56:03.580 --> 00:56:08.000
That's what they called
newmamlakstein which appeared

00:56:08.000 --> 00:56:12.740 position:56%
by the end of the Ottoman period but
in the modern times, they abandoned

00:56:12.740 --> 00:56:15.440
that type of architecture
and they prefer

00:56:15.440 --> 00:56:17.410
of course the modern architecture.

00:56:17.410 --> 00:56:21.400
To my knowledge, as I mentioned, it
was only the effort of Hassan Fatri

00:56:21.400 --> 00:56:24.970
who was trying to revive it again.

00:56:30.790 --> 00:56:33.090
&gt;&gt;AUDIENCE MEMBER: (inaudible)

00:57:09.100 --> 00:57:13.040
&gt;&gt;HEBA: Yeah, we actually have a
problem in Islamic architecture

00:57:13.040 --> 00:57:17.870
