00:57:17.870 --> 00:57:19.170
We don't know him.

00:57:19.170 --> 00:57:20.470
He did not record his name.

00:57:20.470 --> 00:57:25.060
He did not mention anything
to help us identify him.

00:57:25.060 --> 00:57:27.450
So, most of the time,
he was anonymous.

00:57:27.450 --> 00:57:31.030
Unless we found, for example in
the madrasa of the Sultan Hasan,

00:57:31.030 --> 00:57:33.420
we found the name of the
architect and the decorator.

00:57:33.420 --> 00:57:39.320
On the minaret of the madrassa on
- on the minaret of iron chaif,

00:57:39.320 --> 00:57:42.040
we found also the name
of the architect.

00:57:42.040 --> 00:57:47.040
But, those were just a few examples
of names that we managed to find.

00:57:47.040 --> 00:57:50.420
Other than this, they
remained anonymous.

00:57:50.420 --> 00:57:53.210
&gt;&gt;AUDIENCE MEMBER: (inaudible)

00:57:53.210 --> 00:57:54.510
&gt;&gt;HEBA: Probably yes.

00:57:54.510 --> 00:57:57.030
Probably they were
considered as craftsmen,

00:57:57.030 --> 00:58:00.470
not like the elite of that society.

00:58:00.470 --> 00:58:02.380
So they were not recognized.

00:58:02.380 --> 00:58:04.150
Even Sunan.

00:58:04.150 --> 00:58:07.910
Sunan the elder and Sunan the
younger had their own architecture

00:58:07.910 --> 00:58:11.660
in Egypt- had their own
fingerprints in Egypt.

00:58:11.660 --> 00:58:15.610
Maybe by the Ottoman period,
that they paid attention

00:58:15.610 --> 00:58:21.100
to mention the name of the
architect and to commemorate him

00:58:21.100 --> 00:58:25.520
in history and in architecture too.

